      /* view for red-black trees */
      

      11
      rb == self = null & n=0 & bh = 1 & cl = 0 
      

      12
      	or self::node * l::rb * r::rb & cl = 1 & n = 1 + nl + nr & bhl = bh & bhr = bh
      

      13
      	or self::node * l::rb * r::rb & cl = 0 & n = 1 + nl + nr & bhl = bhr & bh = 1 + bhl
      

      14
      	inv n >= 0 & bh >= 1 & 0 <= cl <= 1;

      89

      91
      			return false;
      

      92

      236

      /* function to delete the smalles element in a rb and then rebalance */
      

      295
      int remove_min(ref node x)
      

      296
      

      297
      	requires x::rb & x != null & 0 <= cl <= 1
      

      298
      	ensures x'::rb & cl = 1 & 0 <= cl2 <= 1
      

      299
      		or x'::rb & bh-1 <= bh2 <= bh & cl = 0;
      

      300
              /*
      

      301
      	requires x::rb & x != null 
      

      302
          case { cl=1 -> ensures x'::rb;
      

      303
                 cl=0 -> ensures x'::rb & bh-1 <= bh2 <= bh;
      

      304
                 (cl<0 | cl>1) -> ensures false;
      

      305
          }
      

      306
      */
      

      307
      {
      

      308
      	int v1;
      

      309
      

      310
      	if (x.left == null)
      

      311
      	{
      

      312
      		int tmp = x.val;
      

      313
      

      314
      		if (is_red(x.right))
      

      315
      			x.right.color = 0; 
      

      316
      		x = x.right;
      

      317
      	
      

      318
      		return tmp;
      

      319
      	}
      

      320
      	else 
      

      321
      	{
      

      322
      		v1 = remove_min(x.left);
      

      323
      

      324
      		//rebalance 
      

      325
      		if (bh(x.left) < bh(x.right))
      

      326
      		{
      

      327
      			if (is_black(x.left))
      

      328
      			{
      

      329
      				if (is_red(x.right))
      

      330
      				{
      

      331
      					if (x.right.left != null)
      

      332
                                              {
      

      333
      						x = del_2(x.left, x.right.left, x.right.right);
      

      334
                                                      return v1;
      

      335
                                              }
      

      336
      					else
      

      337
      						return v1;
      

      338
      				}
      

      339
      				else 
      

      340
      				{
      

      341
      					if (is_black(x.right.right))
      

      342
      					{
      

      343
      						if (is_black(x.right.left))
      

      344
      							if (x.color == 0)
      

      345
      							{
      

      346
      								x = del_3(x.left, x.right.left, x.right.right);
      

      347
      								return v1;
      

      348
      							}	
      

      349
      							else
      

      350
      							{
      

      351
      								x = del_4(x.left, x.right.left, x.right.right);
      

      352
      								return v1;
      

      353
      							}
      

      354
      						else
      

      355
      						{
      

      356
      							x = del_5(x.left, x.right.left.left, x.right.left.right, x.right.right, x.color);
      

      357
      							return v1;
      

      358
      						}
      

      359
      					}
      

      360
      					else
      

      361
      					{
      

      362
      						x = del_6(x.left, x.right.left, x.right.right, x.color);
      

      363
      						return v1; 
      

      364
      					}
      

      365
      							
      

      366
      				}
      

      367
      			}

      369
      				return v1;
      

      370
      		}

      			return v1;

      /* function to delete an element in a red black tree */
      

      377
      void del(ref node  x, int a)
      

      378
      

      379
      	requires x::rb & 0 <= cl <= 1
      

      380
      	ensures  x'::rb & cl = 1 & 0 <= cl2 <= 1 
      

      381
      		 or x'::rb & bh-1 <= bh2 <= h & cl = 0 
      

      382
      		 or x'::rb;
      

      383

      384
        requires x::rb 
      

      385

                         or x'::rb;

          }

          assert false;if (x!=null)

            {  assert false;

               {

                        x.left.color = 0;

      			}

      411

      430
      						}
